FBIS4-5379 "dreas069_d_94022" FBIS-EAS-94-069 Daily Report 8 Apr 1994 South Korea Delhi Signs Accord on Supply of Heavy Water Delhi Signs Accord on Supply of Heavy Water BK0804125994 Delhi All India Radio Network in English 1230 GMT 8 Apr 94 BK0804125994 Delhi All India Radio Network English BFN [Text] New Delhi is to supply 100 tons of heavy water for a nuclear power plant in South Korea. Under an agreement signed in Seoul today, the heavy water subject to international atomic energy safeguards will be shipped in 1997-98. The deal worth $23 million is the first major commercial export of heavy water from India which is its leading producer in the world.
